commit.message: Simplified the whole git subtree thing (by not using it =), and turned down some verbose logs in main.rs
Added deployment script, tailwind config, template, etc.

Incrementally updating stuff.

* Added tailwind. Seems to smooth over some CSS issues but Im not sure how much itll get me.
* Limited vec size. This doesn't affect how much is fetched yet but Ill change it later.
* Still need the cron setup w/ commit-if-changed.

Added some debug functionality with fetch/replace html template.

Ultimately this will switch to Tera or Askama, but its fine for now.
In the middle of breaking all sorts of stuff.
More boilerplate, estimate and addr create/update tests.
Updated types in extension and backend.
Added step count to value metadata.
Fixed key/id display and updated todo.
Fixed value layout. Probably needs more work but it's fine for now.
Changed ID scheme after the realization that _all_ expressions will be tagged, not just those for a particular function.
Updated todo, messing with syntax ideas.
Added len for vec/map/data. Fixed tokenize bug.
Made execution cancellable with the addition of threadpool.
Added loop and break, but I forgot I needed if to test conditions...
Removed 1 from index len due to copy/paste =)
Added set for 'places' in maps. Vec and data are likely implemented, need tests.
Removed a bunch of misused macro calls.
Range values no longer stored for load.
Fixed a couple tests incorrectly relying on io markers in def.
Only non-def function calls need to be io wrapped.
Updated TODO, moving to IO lang support to enforce/save myself.
Added file open and delineation between keyable values, or not.

Eval now returns values instead of using the stack.

Still untangling call. I'll continue to make passes over it until things are unified.

Fixed dyn issue.

The new plan is to not use a dynamic trait. Instead, for better or worse, function
variants are going to be put under a 'generic' FuncKind enum, consisting of two variants:
* Native
* User

Native functions will wholly take the place of keyword implementations and builtins, while User
functions will be largely as they are now. This implies that every native function will be a variant
under FuncKind::Native. I think that's fine for a small core of natives, but I'd have to redesign this
(likely entirely) if it were to expand.

This also paves the way for io functions.
Added missing display stuff on Type for map.
Added map literals and required commans on vec literals.

Finally got indexed/dotted access working.

Expressions will likely need to be pulled apart more concretely.
Call is still a bit of a mess. Builtin and keyword ops need to be
unified under the  interface.

Fixed tokenize and parse for dots and indexes.

I think I'll have to do this again to generalize all expressions, but this makes some progress...

My lack of actual expression parsing is now apparent.

I can't evaluate something like v[t.a], where t is (T (a: number), without it.
Numeric indexes like v[10] or v[ten] work as expected, but I have to make expr
Added vec type, op, values, tokenization and new allocation.
Merged syntax highlight/lang provision and LSP into single extension.
